def greet(name: str) -> str:
    """Return a friendly greeting message."""
    return f"Hello, {name}! Welcome to this GitHub project."

if __name__ == "__main__":
    user_name = input("Enter your name: ")
    print(greet(user_name))
# Simple Greeting Project

This is a basic Python project that prints a friendly greeting.  
You can clone the repository, run the script, and customize it as you wish.

## How to Run

This is a basic Python project that prints a friendly greeting.  
You can clone the repository, run the script, and customize it as you wish.
